Author:
Vol / Page: 18
Edition:
Quote: I was two beats from the top, and there was shingle all the way. It slid continuously, and all the time I had to bear up hill, to keep a level track. However, we got off `the hill' quite early, put the sheep across Cat Creek at Tarndale, and raced for the homestead. <i>Ibid.</i> 29 But we got our mail, and were glad to be for a day or so `off the hill'. <i>Ibid.</i> 46 Dogs often start work down country at about nine months - sometimes under. That is too young to start a dog on the hill.
